BRAZIL DAYBOOK: Job Creation, Coutinho at the Senate

-- B y   H e l d e r   M a r i n h o
-- 
2011-05-17T03:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-17/brazil-daybook-job-creation-coutinho-at-the-senate.html
Labor Minister Carlos Lupi announces
 Brazil ’s formal job creation statistics for the month of April
and speaks to reporters in Brasilia about the outlook for the
country’s labor market. Brazil created 92,675 jobs in March, the
fewest since a seasonal loss of jobs in December.  GOVERNMENT:
*President Dilma Rousseff meets Sweden Prime Minister Fredrik
Reinfeldt in Brasilia at 10 a.m.
*Finance Minister Guido Mantega arrives in Brasilia at 11 a.m.
and has internal meetings
*Central bank president Alexandre Tombini meets Swedish business
executives in the afternoon in Brasilia.  WHAT TO WATCH:
*BNDES President Luciano Coutinho attends a public meeting at
the Senate in Brasilia at 9:30 a.m.
*Trade Minister Fernando Pimentel, the head of Brazils tax
agency Carlos Barreto and Vice President Michel Temer speak at
an event in Brasilia about  tax reform , starting at 10 a.m.
*Santander Annual Latin American Equity Conference in London
*Marfrig to hold first-quarter conference calls at 10 a.m. in
Portuguese and 12 p.m.
*Vale holds an extraordinary meeting of shareholders in  Rio de
Janeiro 
*Apimec Rio hosts a meeting with Eletrobras executives in Rio de
Janeiro at 5:30 p.m.  ECONOMY:
*Fipe weekly  consumer price index  at 5 a.m.
*Caged formal job creation at 11 a.m.  EQUITIES:
*CCR (CCRO3 BS) posted first-quarter net income of 175.2 million
reais
*Copersucar (3657049Z BZ) hired banks including Itau to handle
its initial public offering, according to a person with
knowledge of the situation
*JHSF (JHSF3 BZ) forecast new projects worth 2 billion reais in
2011 and 2012  MARKETS
*The Bovespa index fell 0.6 percent to 62,829.68.
*The real rose 0.1 percent to 1.6348 per dollar.  To contact the reporter on this story: 
